    <title>__HAL_FLASH_HALF_CYCLE_ACCESS_DISABLE</title>
<indexterm><primary>__HAL_FLASH_HALF_CYCLE_ACCESS_DISABLE</primary><secondary>FLASH Half Cycle</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>FLASH Half Cycle</primary><secondary>__HAL_FLASH_HALF_CYCLE_ACCESS_DISABLE</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>#define __HAL_FLASH_HALF_CYCLE_ACCESS_DISABLE( )   (FLASH-&gt;ACR &amp;= (~<link linkend="_group___peripheral___registers___bits___definition_1ga6e66d0fa94c019e9c27a3d79e8228cd9">FLASH_ACR_HLFCYA</link>))</computeroutput></para><para>

<para>Disable the FLASH half cycle access. </para>
</para>

<para><note><title>Note</title>

<para>half cycle access can only be used with a low-frequency clock of less than 8 MHz that can be obtained with the use of HSI or HSE but not of PLL. </para>
</note>

